Reasoning: The paper discusses predicting outcomes of the Research Excellence Framework (REF) using the departmental h-index, which is a measure of research productivity and impact. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given that the paper focuses on evaluating the accuracy of previous predictions, it is less likely to belong to the sub-categories of cybersecurity and cryptography and security.
